Stock index futures recorded a volatile session as dealers fought off
worries over political uncertainty in the UK and fears of a rise in US
interest rates.
The June contract on the FT-SE 100 finished at 3,103 having in the course of
the session been at both a premium and a substantial discount to cash.
Volume was 17,876 contracts.
In the traded options, turnover fell back to 29,439 contracts of which
11,184 was dealt in the FT-SE 100 volume and 3,908 in the Euro FT-SE option.
Abbey National was the busiest stock option.
